c":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"A real hook invocation path (stdin -> parser -> trace sink) produces the expected trace artifact when malformed input is supplied.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: 'Real hook invocation path' and 'trace artifact' together describe end-to-end execution: real stdin piped into a real process, a real (on-disk or socket) trace sink, and an artifact that persists after the process exits. REAL-INFRA: Yes. The artifact is produced by the real pipeline; an in-process test cannot produce or verify a real artifact written by a real subprocess. MOCK-HIDE: An in-process integration test would substitute the trace sink with a mock, making it impossible to verify the artifact format, file location, or that it survives process exit. LLM-DEP: None. REJECTION-GATE: Integration was considered but disqualified by 'real hook invocation path' — the behavior's failure mode includes artifact production by a real process, which only a System-level test reproduces.","test_description":"Invoke the hook binary end-to-end with malformed JSON on stdin and a real trace sink configured (e.g., pointing to a temp file or local socket). After the process exits, read the trace artifact and assert it contains a well-formed `json_parse_failed` record with the required diagnostic fields — verifying the full stdin→parser→sink pipeline under real execution conditions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.76,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Regression tests distinguish malformed-JSON failures from valid-markdown payloads, preventing false attribution to markdown content itself.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure mode is a false-positive in test attribution — the test suite incorrectly blames markdown for a parse failure that only occurs with truly malformed JSON. This is a property of the parser's behavior on two distinct input classes, testable at a single function boundary. REAL-INFRA: None required; the parser is called in-process with two input sets. MOCK-HIDE: Nothing meaningful to mock. LLM-DEP: None. REJECTION-GATE: Integration was considered but disqualified: both markdown-valid and truly-malformed inputs exercise only the parser's own logic, not a cross-module handoff. The distinguishing assertion ('these succeed, those fail') is fully visible at Unit level.","test_description":"Run the hook input parser against a parametrized matrix of inputs: one set of valid JSON strings with heavy markdown content (must all succeed), and one set of truly malformed JSON strings (must all produce a parse error). Assert the two sets produce strictly different outcomes — success vs. failure — with no overlap, confirming markdown alone never triggers a parse error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.78,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9613,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9613},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b79053d6-cd8e-404e-aee6-fa58860d7d4f","uuid":"38b964e4-2473-4ab0-99de-ce6da3c87fab"}
